    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-03-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="476"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d476">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Clayton</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-03-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2173.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to former correspondence relating to
                    the case of Conductor L. C. Crutcher,<note n="a" xml:id="d476fna">See <ref
                            target="frus1903#pg_645">Foreign Relations, 1903, p. 645</ref> et
                        seq.</note> I now have the honor to transmit a copy of correspondence
                    between the embassy and Jose Lopez Moctezuma, local attorney of the Mexican
                    Central Railway Company, from which it will be seen that the superior tribunal
                    of the State of San Luis Potosi has confirmed the decision of the court of first
                    instance, by which Mr. Crutcher is relieved of all responsibility.</p>
                <p>As at present advised, I conclude that no further action in this case is required
                    by the embassy.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Powell Clayton.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <persName type="from">Licentiate Moctezuma</persName> to Mr. <persName
                                type="to">Clayton</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexican Centeal Railway Company</hi> (<hi
                                    rend="smallcaps">Limited</hi>),<lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Legal Department</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mexico, D. F.</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-10">
                                <hi rend="italic">February 10, 1904</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Distinguished Sir</hi>: The company’s attorney at San
                        Luis Potosi informs me that the decision pronounced in the case of Conductor
                        Crutcher has been confirmed by the superior tribunal of the State of San
                        Luis Potosi. Mr. Crutcher has, therefore, been released, free from all
                        responsibility.</p>
                    <p>I remain, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">José Lopez Moctezuma</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Attorney</hi>.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
